    "body": "<span class=\"solution-visible-txt\">All submissions for this problem are available.</span><p align=\"justify\">\nRG loves to create chaos. He has decided to create chaos in the state of <i>Mysteryland</i>.\n</p>\n<p align=\"justify\">\nThere are <b>n</b> cities in the state of  <i>Mysteryland</i> indexed from 1 to <b>n</b>. Initially, there are <b>m</b> cities that are already chaotic.<br />\nNow, RG can create chaos in a city with index <b>i</b> which is not chaotic only if there is at least one chaotic city with index <b>j</b> such that:<br /><br />\n<center><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Absolute_difference\">absolute difference </a>(<b>i</b>, <b>j</b>) =1.</center><br />\n<br /><br />\nNow, help him find the possible number of ways of making all the cities chaotic.\n</p>\n<h3>Input</h3>\n<p align=\"justify\">\nThe first line contains a single integer <b>T</b>, denoting the number of testcases. The descriptions of <b>T</b> test cases follow.</p>\n<p align=\"justify\">The first line of each test case contains two space separated integers <b>n</b> and <b>m</b> where <b>n</b> represents total number of cities in Mysteryland and <b>m</b> represents the number of cities that are already chaotic.<br />Next line contains <b>m</b> distinct integers lying between 1 and <b>n</b> (both inclusive) representing the indices of the cities that are already chaotic.</p>\n<h3>Output</h3>\n<p align=\"justify\">\nFor each Test case, print the number of ways he can make all cities chaotic. As the answer can be very large, print it modulo <b>1000000007</b>.\u00a0</p>\n<h3>Constraints</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>T</b> \u2264 <b>1000.</b></li>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>m</b> \u2264 <b>n</b> \u2264 <b>1000</b>\n</li></ul>\n<h3>Example</h3>\n<pre>\n<b>Input:</b>\n3\n5 1\n1\n4 2\n1 3\n4 1\n2\n\n<b>Output:</b>\n1\n2\n3\n</pre><h3>Explanation</h3>\n<p align=\"justify\"><b>Example case 1.</b> There is only one way of making all the cities chaotic. RG can make the cities chaotic in the order {2, 3, 4, 5}.</p>\n<p align=\"justify\"><b>Example case 2.</b> There are two ways of making all the cities chaotic. RG can make the cities chaotic in the order {2, 4} or {4, 2}.</p>\n<p align=\"justify\"><b>Example case 3.</b> There are three ways of making all the cities chaotic. RG can make the cities chaotic in the order {1,3,4} , {3,1,4} or {3,4,1}.</p>\n",
